benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Retrieve bundle custom fields

covered: Valid GET requests produce 200 with an array of CustomField objects (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC11, TC12, TC15).
Empty response scenario with bundle having no custom fields (TC04).
400 responses for invalid bundleId format and invalid/malformed audit parameters (TC06, TC07, TC13).
401 Unauthorized when no valid authentication token is provided (TC08).
503 Service unavailability due to database or audit service issues (TC09, TC16).
Extra, unexpected query parameters are ignored (TC10).
Security tests covering SQL injection in bundleId (TC17) and XSS in audit parameter (TC18).
Concurrency scenario with multiple concurrent requests (TC19).
Response structure checks for machine-readability and JSON array (TC20).
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling under high load is not tested.
Caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control headers and conditional requests) is not tested.
403 Forbidden scenario (insufficient permissions) is not explicitly tested.
Additional security vectors beyond SQLi/XSS are not covered.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page/size) to verify correct paging and metadata in responses.
Include rate-limiting tests (expecting 429) and throttling behavior under bursty traffic.
Add caching tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and If-None-Match handling to verify caching semantics.
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient-permission scenarios.
Expand security tests to cover more attack vectors beyond SQLi and XSS.
